body:
Carol Danvers!Witch headcanon

|| @determinedundertrollspapypop this goes out to you lol ||

  • She has a lot of trouble controlling her powers due to her emotions
  • If she’s feeling one particular emotion, her powers go out of whack and causes everything around her start to shake and rumble
  • Goose is her familiar (obviously)
  • Goose follows her every whim
  • Goose starts to hiss as a sign of danger when something wrong is about to happen
  • Goose talks to Carol telepathically so when others are around Carol, it’s seen as a one sided conversation
  • Carol is constantly practicing her magic, training to be the best she can be
  • She has a book of spells that she only read half way and somehow knows each and every spell in it. Even though she has only taken a quickly glance at what was typed
  • She has a broom and the stick is a bright red with a big yellow bow that’s formed in a star right where the bristles start. The bristles are also a deep blue
  • The broom’s handle has the word, ‘Mar-Vell’ caved into it
  • A bright yellow aura starts to radiate off of her when she is using her powers with extreme concentration. Or when her emotions start to go haywire
  • Her eyes too, start to glow
  • Once Carol gets a hold on her emotions and can handle it properly, it’s when her true powers come out and is really shown
  • She is a lot more powerful than she thinks

summary: Why is it that if someone does not like Captain Marvel or Brie Larson they are automatically a bitter, whiny, sexist, white boy?...
body: Why is it that if someone does not like Captain Marvel or Brie Larson they are automatically a bitter, whiny, sexist, white boy? But Wonder Woman and Gal Gadot are generally well received? Could it be that maybe Captain Marvel just wasn’t as good a movie and Brie Larson isn’t as likeable a person and have nothing to do with sex, race, or feminism?
